rts faced the task of applying legal norms from the Nazi period under fundamentally altered conditions. This study describes the ways they dealt with this challenge using the examples of family and labor law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aAbstammungsrecht. 4aArbeitsrecht. 4aEherecht. 4aEntnazifizierung. 4aJustizgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aHistory of justice.  adenazification.  alabor law.  amarital law.  aparentage law.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2017z9783110547764oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104026500 cprintz978311040254440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110402582zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110402582zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110402582.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3 DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-GOA